---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Inflation Calculator
description: Estimate how inflation may affect future prices and the purchasing power of money over time.
navKey: tools
tags: tools
scripts:
  - /assets/tools/inflation.js
---

<div class="calculator-page">
    <section class="page-hero page-hero-compact">
        <p class="eyebrow">Purchasing power</p>

        <h1>Inflation Calculator</h1>

        <p class="hero-copy">
            Estimate how inflation may change future prices
            and reduce the purchasing power of money over time.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section
        class="calculator-card"
        data-inflation-calculator
        aria-label="Inflation calculator"
    >
        <div class="calculator-input-grid">
            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="currentAmount">
                    Amount today
                </label>

                <input
                    id="currentAmount"
                    type="number"
                    min="0.01"
                    step="any"
                    value="10000"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                >
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="inflationRate">
                    Annual inflation rate
                </label>

                <div class="calculator-input-suffix">
                    <input
                        id="inflationRate"
                        type="number"
                        min="0"
                        step="0.01"
                        value="3"
                        inputmode="decimal"
                    >

                    <span aria-hidden="true">%</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-field">
                <label for="inflationYears">
                    Number of years
                </label>

                <input
                    id="inflationYears"
                    type="number"
                    min="0.01"
                    step="any"
                    value="20"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                >
            </div>
        </div>

        <p
            class="calculator-error"
            id="inflationError"
            role="alert"
        ></p>

        <div
            class="calculator-results"
            aria-live="polite"
        >
            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Future equivalent cost
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="futureCost"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small>
                    Future amount needed to buy the same thing
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Future purchasing power
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="purchasingPower"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small>
                    What the original amount may buy later
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="calculator-result">
                <span class="calculator-result-label">
                    Cumulative inflation
                </span>

                <strong
                    class="calculator-result-value"
                    id="cumulativeInflation"
                >
                    —
                </strong>

                <small>
                    Total estimated price increase
                </small>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="calculator-explanation">
            <h2>How this inflation calculator works</h2>

            <p>
                The calculator applies the same annual inflation rate
                throughout the selected period. Actual inflation changes
                from year to year, sometimes politely and sometimes with
                all the subtlety of a grocery receipt.
            </p>

            <div class="formula-grid">
                <div class="formula-card">
                    <span>Future equivalent cost</span>

                    <code>
                        Amount × (1 + inflation rate)^years
                    </code>
                </div>

                <div class="formula-card">
                    <span>Future purchasing power</span>

                    <code>
                        Amount ÷ (1 + inflation rate)^years
                    </code>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p>
                Future equivalent cost estimates how many dollars may be
                needed later to purchase what the entered amount buys today.
                Future purchasing power estimates what the same unchanged
                dollar amount may be worth in today's terms.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <p class="tool-disclaimer">
        For educational purposes only. Results are estimates and assume
        a constant inflation rate. Actual prices and inflation rates vary.
    </p>
</div>
